              <p class="case-study-summary">
                Designed a RAG workflow that indexes long Telegram histories and returns semantically relevant
                answers instead of brittle keyword matches.
              </p>
              <ul class="case-study-points">
                <li>Chunking and embedding strategy built for messy conversational data.</li>
                <li>Search tuned for context recovery, not vanity demos.</li>
                <li>Useful where institutional knowledge lives in chat, not in docs.</li>
              </ul>
              <div class="project-links">
                <a href="https://github.com/luvor" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="project-link">
